FeedPackage.Description: MiniState is an attempt to provide simple abstraction layer to reading and writing state information like HTTP cookies to minimise cookie size and increase the quality of code and security.
FeedPackage.Summary: MiniState is an attempt to provide simple abstraction layer to reading and writing state information like HTTP cookies to minimise cookie size and increase the quality of code and security.
FeedPackage.Title: ministate

FeedPackage.Description: MiniState simplifies managing cookie information or other string based property stores. MiniState attempts to minimise the amount of data required to store values, protect values from tampering using HMAC validation, reduce the risk of replay attacks by specifying a valid lifetime of the values and mitigate the difficulties of handling cookies set by previous revisions by using version numbers.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: This is a beta release and may not be suitable for production environments.

Structured log events are written to sinks and each sink is responsible for writing it to its own backend, database, store etc. This sink delivers the data to Graylog2, a NoSQL search engine.
